They went into the reception room familiar to Pierre, with two Italian windows opening in- to the conservatory, with its large bust and full- length portrait of Catherine the Great. The same people were still sitting here in almost the same positions as before, whispering to one another. All became silent and turned to look at the pale tear-worn Anna Mikhylovna as she entered, and at the big stout figure of Pierre who, hanging his head, meekly followed her.
